Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a pale-red pottery vessel, the fabric is grey in section, the interior is thickly encrusted with a dark-brown/grey deposit, the exterior is covered with light-brown slip, one line of black-painted demotic text with a large symbol beneath.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393861) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393861)
